{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Implement mandatory substance testing during child welfare checks",
        "additional_details": "We believe that by enforcing mandatory testing, social workers and law enforcement officers can make more informed decisions regarding the immediate removal of a child from potentially dangerous settings. This approach could also provide an objective basis to court decisions regarding custody and make sure the welfare of the child is upheld as a paramount concern. We think it is imperative to create and enforce clear policies for conducting mandatory drug and alcohol testing during child welfare checks.",
        "background": "In our view, we must ensure the environment a child is being placed into is safe, and therefore that it is both logical and crucial to incorporate mandatory substance testing during welfare checks following reports of substance abuse.",
